**Section 1: User Story
**

**1.1** **Epic Story**

As a Notice Processing Officer who needs to follow up against notices in the OCMS, I want the OCMS to allow me to revive the temporary/permanent suspension/reduction of a notice, so that the notice can resume processing according to the automated processing workflows in Appendix B of Annex 1A.

**1.2 User Stories **

![](data:image/x-emf;base64,)

**1.3 Key Functions &amp; Features**

| Functions | Description |
| --- | --- |
| Revive Suspensions Function | Suspension Revival is a function in OCMS that lifts or removes an existing Temporary Suspension (TS) or a Permanent Suspension (PS) on a Notice. Predefined Revival Codes are used to indicate the reason for lifting the suspension. |
| Manual Revival via the OCMS Staff Portal | The OCMS Staff Portal provides a user interface for authorised OICs to manually lift Suspensions. |
| Auto Revival during scheduled batch job processing | Auto Revivals are triggered by the Notice Revival scheduled batch job (cron job). Its key functions are to: Lift the existing suspension Update the existing suspension record in the database Identify whether the lifting of the Suspension Code requires a follow-up action (eg. Re-apply the same TS Suspension Code or to initiate a refund) Initiate the follow-up action if required |
| Revival initiated by PLUS System | OCMS provides an API that allows PLUS users to lift an existing TS or PS on a Notice based on the outcome of the appeal review. |

**Section 2 - Revive Suspension Function**

**2.1 Use case**

- The Revive Suspension function lifts or removes a Temporary Suspension or Permanent Suspension on a Notice for various reasons. Common scenarios include:TS has expired,
- To change the suspension reason,
- To redirect the Notice to another Offender, 
- When the Offender’s updated particulars has been received, or 
- To speed up Notice processing

- Notice Revival is initiated when:Notice Processing Officers from EPU manually trigger the revival function via the OCMS Staff Portal b.
- OCMS backend auto triggers revival function during Notice Revival batch job processing
- Appeal Processing Officers from PLU manually trigger the revival function via the PLUS Staff Portal 
- During Revival, the Revival function will:Lift the existing TS and PS 
- Update the existing Suspension record with the revival date and Revival Reason
- Detect whether the PS or TS Suspension Code to be lifted requires follow-up actions, such as to re-apply the same TS Suspension Code or to initiate a refund
- Initiate the follow-up action if required
**2.2 High-Level Processing Flow**

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

NOTE: Due to page size limit, the full-sized image is appended.

![](data:image/x-emf;base64,)

| No. | Process | Description |
| --- | --- | --- |
| | Pre-conditions | Manual apply Revival from Staff Portal: EPU user manually apply Revival from OCMS Staff Portal PLU user manually apply Revival from the PLUS system Staff Portal. Auto lift Suspensions by the OCMS Backend: OCMS backend runs the Notice Revival scheduled batch job to lift Suspensions based on pre-defined rules. |
| 1 | OCMS and PLUS Staff Portals check if the revival request is allowed | The OCMS Staff Portal and PLUS Staff Portal will perform an initial check to determine whether the Revival is allowed. For example, Revival is not allowed if the OIC has no permission to trigger the function. If the Revival is not allowed, the Portal will display an error prompt in the UI to inform the User that it is not allowed. The process ends. If the Revival is allowed, the Portal will proceed to Step 2. |
| 2 | OCMS and PLUS Staff Portals proceed to submit Revival request via API | The OCMS Staff Portal will call the OCMS backend API to process the Revival request. The PLUS Staff Portal will call the PLUS backend API to request for suspension. The PLUS backend will then call the OCMS backend API to process the Revival request. |
| 3 | OCMS backend checks if Revival is allowed | OCMS backend proceeds to validate the request to determine if the requested Revival can be performed. The validation of the request is based on the rules of suspension which have been pre-defined in the backend. If Revival is not allowed, the OCMS backend responds with an error message to the requesting system and the process ends. If Revival is allowed, the OCMS backend proceeds to lift the suspension, update the Notice information and respond to the requesting system with the revival outcome. |
| 4 | Check for Follow-Up Action | OCMS backend continues to check if any additional action is required after the revival. If no follow-up action is needed, the process ends If follow-up action is needed, OCMS backend proceeds to initiate the function required for the follow-up action, for example, to re-apply the same Suspension Code. The process concludes after the follow-up action is triggered. |

**2.3 Applying Revival to TS &amp; PS**

| Aspect | Temporary Suspension (TS) | Permanent Suspension (PS) |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Manual Revival | Initiated from OCMS Staff Portal Initiated from PLUS Staff Portal | Initiated from OCMS Staff Portal Initiated from PLUS Staff Portal |
| Auto Revival | Triggered by OCMS backend when the TS reaches its expiry date | Triggered by OCMS backend when a new PS is applied to replace an existing PS |
| Common Triggers | TS has expired Officers have reviewed and determined the suspension is no longer valid | Officers have reviewed and determined the PS is no longer valid |
| Revival Code | Required, to indicate reason for lifting TS | Required, to indicate reason for lifting PS |
| Backend Actions During Revival | Check if TS is HST Lift the TS Update database with revival details | Check whether request is to lift more than 1 PS per Notice Lift the PS |
| Post-Revival Follow-up Actions | Check if TS is a Looping Suspension to re-apply TS if required Check if Hirer/Driver particulars submission has been approved/rejected to determine whether TS-PDP needs to be re-applied Check if Next Processing Date has passed to determine whether the Notice needs to be sent to LTA, MHA or DataHive to prepare for the Next Processing Stage Reverse a Reduction if TS-RED is lifted | Check if Notice is paid to determine whether the refund identified date should be added to the Notice (for MVP only) Check if Notice is paid to determine whether refund should be initiated (post-MVP) |

**2.5 Revival Codes **

- The list below outlines all the Revival Codes that can be processed by OCMS. 

- Each Code indicates a reason for lifting the suspension. 

- The list of Revival Codes will be stored under the “Revival Reason” Reference Code list, which can be manged via the Standard Code module in the OCMS Staff Portal. *Refer to Section 5 of the OCMS 39 – Parameters Management Functional Document.
*

| Code | Reason for Revival | Scenario |
| --- | --- | --- |
| CSR | Change suspension reason | A new suspension reason has been identified, and the existing suspension needs to be replaced. |
| CWN | Cancelled wrong notice | PS was incorrectly applied to the Notice |
| DPU | Driver's Particulars Updated | TS suspension was lifted as OCMS received the updated Driver’s particulars. |
| HAV | HST Address Verified | The TS-HST suspension was lifted after OCMS received the updated Offender address and the new address has been verified by the OIC |
| OPU | Owner's Particulars Updated | TS suspension was lifted as OCMS received the updated Owner’s particulars. |
| OTH | Others | Suspension was lifted due to other reasons. |
| PSR | Permanent suspension revival | PS has been lifted. |
| RDN | Redirect notice | TS was lifted to allow the Notice to be redirected to another offender. |
| SPO | Suspension period is over | TS was lifted as the suspension has expired. |
| SUP | Speed-up processing | TS was lifted to expedite Notice processing. |
| SYS | System issue resolved | TS was lifted as the system issue has been resolved. |

**2.6 Suspension Revival Rules **

**2.6.1 Global Rules for Revival**

| Condition | Rule | Description |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Displaying Revival in the Staff Portal | Display the most recent suspension | Suspensions which have been revived should not be displayed in the View Notice Overview tab Revival details will be displayed in the View Suspension Details tab |
| OCMS users can lift all TS and PS codes, regardless of whether the suspension was applied by OCMS or PLUS users. | Depends on Suspension Code | Authorised OCMS OICs can lift TS and PS Suspensions. The exception is TS-HST which can only be revived by OCMS OICs via the OCMS Staff Portal’s HST module. |
| PLUS users can lift all TS and PS codes, regardless of whether the suspension was applied by OCMS or PLUS users. | Depends on Suspension Code | Authorised PLUS PLMs can lift TS and PS Suspensions. The exception is TS-HST which can only be revived by OCMS OICs via the OCMS Staff Portal’s HST module. |
| Auto revive when applying a new PS Code to a Notice with an existing PS code | Allowed | Authorised OCMS and PLUS Users are allowed to apply a new PS Suspension Code to a Notice with an existing PS. When a new ERP Reason of Suspension PS is triggered via the OCMS or PLUS Staff Portal, OCMS will revive the existing PS with the revival code '-PSR' before applying the new PS automatically to all Notices with existing and active PS codes. The CRS Reason of Suspension (PS-FP or PS-PRA) cannot be applied to Notices with existing and active PS codes. The only exceptions to (3) are Notices with the following existing active PS suspensions which allow PS-FP or PS-PRA without reviving the existing PS: DIP FOR MID RIP RP2 To allow CRS suspensions (PS-FP and PS-PRA) to be applied WITHOUT PS REVIVAL. i.e. the ERP reason of Suspension will be updated as PS-DIP and CRS Reason of Suspension will be updated as PS-FP. For non-CRS suspension (e.g. PS-APP, APE) applied over special notices (DIP, FOR, MID, RIP, RP2), PS revival IS REQUIRED. |
| Global revival of all active TS Suspensions for one Notice Reviving TS for a notice will revive all TS suspensions on that Notice (except TS-HST and TS-RED) | Allowed | Authorised OCMS and PLUS Users are allowed to trigger a one-time lifting of all active TS-es that have been applied to a Notice. The exceptions are: TS-HST which can only be revived by OCMS OICs via the OCMS Staff Portal’s HST module TS-RED which can only be revived by PLUS OICs via the PLUS Staff Portal |
| Global revival of all active TS and PS Suspensions for one Notice | Allowed | Authorised OCMS and PLUS Users are allowed to trigger a one-time lifting of all active TS-es and PS that have been applied to a Notice. |
| Revive PS for multiple Notices | Not allowed | Authorised OCMS and PLUS Users can only lift PS for one Notice at a time. Users are not allowed to revive PS for multiple Notices. |
| Revive TS for multiple Notices | Allowed | Authorised OCMS and PLUS Users can lift multiple TS-es for multiple Notices at a time. The same revival reason and revival date will be used. |
| Revive Notices with PS-FP | Allowed | Authorised OCMS and PLUS Users can lift the PS-FP suspension for paid notices. The lifting of the suspension will trigger the OCMS backend to initiate a refund. Note: For OCMS MVP, OCMS will only store the date that the refund has been identified. |
| After revival, the Notice will resume from the point at which it was suspended. | Depends on: Whether there is a pre-defined follow-up action that needs to be performed Whether the Next Processing Date has passed | After a TS or PS is lifted, OCMS will check the Notice’s Next Processing Date. If the Next Processing Date is in the future, the Notice will remain in the workflow until it is time to prepare for the next processing stage. If the Next Processing Date has passed, the Notice will be picked up by another scheduled job that submits the vehicles’ particulars to LTA or offender’s particulars to MHA and/or DataHive to retrieve the latest details in preparation for the next processing stage. |
| Send eNA eNotification and eReminders after Suspension is lift | Not allowed | After a Notice is revived, the OCMS backend will not send eNA or eReminder SMS/email notifications for the Last Processing Stage, even if they have been sent. eNotification and eReminders will resume when notices move to the next processing stage. |

**2.6.2 Suspension Code Rules **

- The OCMS backend maintains a set of rules governing the revival of TS-es and PS-es.

- The rules will include: Which codes can be applied by PLUS System Users 
- Which codes can be applied by OCMS System Users 
- Which codes can only be applied by the OCMS backend system 
- Follow-actions required after lifting specific Suspension Codes 
- Suspension Revival Rules 
![](data:image/x-emf;base64,)

MGG proposes to store the rules listed in the database, so that the backend system uses the data to validate the TS requests and permissions. 

**2.7 Validating Revival Requests
2.7.1 Key Validation Principles **

- All requests to Revive suspensions will be validated. 

- When a Revival request is initiated from a Staff Portal (OCMS or PLUS):The Staff Portal will perform the first round of validation based on:Whether the User has permission to initiate the Revival 
- Whether the Suspension Codes for the Notice(s) selected can be revived
- Whether the User is attempting to revive PS for multiple Notices 

- If the Notice(s) are determined to be eligible for Revival, the Portal will trigger the Revival request to the OCMS backend which will also perform another round of validation against all rules for Revival. 

- When a Revival request is initiated from the Backend, for example upon TS expiry, the OCMS backend will also validate the request to determine if the Revival can be applied 

**2.7.2 Validating Revival Requests in the Staff Portal (OCMS and PLUS)**

- The Staff Portal performs first-level validation to provide immediate feedback and prevent invalid revival requests from being sent to the backend system.

- The Staff Portal submits revival requests to the backend only if the first-level validation confirms that the conditions for revival are met.

- This approach improves user experience as it:Provides instant feedback so users know immediately if Revival is permitted
- Guides users to deselect invalid Notices before submission
- Checks known revival rules (e.g. multiple Notices with PS suspensions) upfront
- Prevent obviously invalid requests from reaching the backend
- The following checks will be performed on the UI side, based on valid offence notice data received from the backend:

| What to Validate in UI | Description |
| --- | --- |
| User Permission | The Portal checks whether the User has permission to initiate the Revival. |
| Suspension Codes to Revive | The Portal checks whether the User is attempting to revive a TS-HST suspension. |
| Multiple Notices with PS | The Portal checks whether the User is attempting to revive more than 1 Notice with a Permanent Suspension. |

**2.7.3 Validating Requests and Performing Revival in the OCMS Backend**

- The OCMS Backend is the main processor for Revival requests. 

- The Revival function in the OCMS Backend can be triggered by the following sources:

| Source | Scenario |
| --- | --- |
| OCMS Backend | Auto trigger Revival when the TS has expired |
| OCMS Staff Portal | OICs manual Revive one or more TS and or PS suspensions after investigation |
| PLUS Staff Portal | PLMs manual Revive one or more TS or PS suspensions for specific reasons after reviewing the Appeals. |

- When the OCMS Backend receives the request to perform TS, it will check and enforce:

| Rules | Description |
| --- | --- |
| Authentication of Source and Permission | Source has a valid token for the API call Source is allowed to trigger suspension for the given Suspension Code |
| Global Rules | Suspension Code to Revive is not TS-HST |
| Revival Code Specific Rules | Requestor has permission to Revive with the specific Revival Code Suspension Code to Revive is not TS-HST |

- The Backend validation serves as the final safeguard that ensures that the system’s suspension rules are enforced consistently and securely.

- In additional to validating the Revival requests, OCMS will also identify the necessary follow-up action required for each Suspension Code after Revival and trigger the action. 
- The Backend process is illustrated in the flow below. Sub-flows are based on Section 2.7.2 Suspension Code Rules.

**2.8 OCMS Backend Revive Response Scenarios **

| Scenario | Response Message |
| --- | --- |
| API authentication failed (JWT) | Invalid JWT token |
| API authentication failed (API key) | Invalid Auth Token |
| sr_no not found in ocms_suspended_notices | Suspension record not found |
| | |
| Suspension is not active (invalid status) | - No active suspension |
| | |
| Notice is under Court Stage (not CPC/CFC) | Notice is under Court processing |
| User is not authorized for TS-HST revival | User not authorised to revive TS-HST |
| TS was revived successfully with no follow-up | TS revived successfully |
| TS was revived and follow-up (e.g., TS-CLV, TS-PDP) reapplied | TS revived and looping {insert suspension type}-{insert suspension code} re-applied |
| PS-FP was revived and refund marked | PS-FP revived and refund date identified |
| Failed to reapply follow-up TS (e.g., TS-CLV reapply error) | Looping {insert suspension type}-{insert suspension code} failed |
| Next Processing Date missing or corrupt | Invalid Next Processing Date |
| Generic internal error during revival | Backend error during revival |

**3.1 Use case**

**Section 3 - OCMS Staff Portal Manual Revival**

- The manual Revive Suspension function in the OCMS Staff Portal allows authorised OICs to lift suspensions on Notices.

- Users can search for the notices using the Staff Portal’s Search Notice function by:Entering search parameters to retrieve one or more Notices
- Uploading a spreadsheet containing a list of notice numbers to retrieve the Notices.

- From the search results, Users can apply revival TS/PS using one of two ways: Select one or more Notices in the Search Result interface and trigger the revive TS/PS operation from the drop-down list to initiate a batch revival. 
- Click on a Notice to view the details and apply the revive TS/PS from the View Notice Details interface 

- OCMS OICs can revive multiple TS or multiple Notices simultaneously.

- For manual revivals, OCMS OICs can only revive 1 PS for 1 Notice at a time. 

- When the revive TS/PS is initiated from the Staff Portal, the Staff Portal validates the revival suspension eligibility of each Notice before redirecting Users to the Revive Suspension Detail Page to: Select the revive TS/PS Suspension Code 
- Input Revival Suspension Remarks, if any
- After the Revive Suspension Details are submitted, OCMS sends the revival suspension details to the OCMS backend for processing. 
- If revive TS/PS is successful, Users will be presented with a success message on screen; an error message will be displayed if the revival of the suspension is not successful.

**Section 4 - Auto Revive in OCMS**

**4.1 Use case**

- The OCMS Backend will only initiate Suspension Revival automatically for selected use cases. 

- When reviving a Notice, the OCMS backend will use a Revival Reason code to indicate the reason of suspension. 
**4.2 Scenarios that Trigger Auto Revive **

| Scenario | Revival Code | Auto Triggered by |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Temporary Suspension Period has expired. | SPO | OCMS Backend |
| New PS is applied to Notice with existing PS | CSR | OCMS Staff Portal PLUS Staff Portal |

**Section 5 – Manual Revival initiated by PLUS**

**5.1 Use case**

- PLMs can initiate Revival via an API provided by OCMS.
- PLMs may initiate a revival under the following circumstances:PLM accepts the appeal and grants a waiver for a paid Notice, triggering revival of the PS-FP suspension (i.e., replacing PS-FP with PS-APP).

- PLM rejects the appeal and lifts the TS, allowing Notice processing to continue.
- During Revival, PLUS will initiate a Revival on the latest Suspension. 
- PLMs can revive multiple TS or multiple Notices simultaneously.

- PLMs user can only revive 1 PS for 1 Notice at a time

When Revival is initiated through the PLUS Staff Portal, the PLUS system shall provide the suspension details, which will be logged in OCMS in the Suspended Notices database table.

- Upon receiving the request, OCMS validates the submitted revival data before performing the Revival.

| 2 | Search for Appeal(s) | The User uses the Search function to retrieve the Appeal Case(s). |
| 3 | Select Notice(s) within an Appeal to revive Suspensions | The user selects the relevant Notice(s) for which suspension(s) are to be revived. |
| 4 | Optional Step: Select Suspensions within a Notice to revive | For Notices with multiple suspensions, the user can specify which suspension(s) within the Notice to revive. |
| 5 | Validate if Revival is allowed | The Staff Portal checks if the selected Notice(s) and suspensions are eligible for revival based on pre-set rules. If Revival is not allowed for one or more Notices, PLUS Staff Portal proceeds to Step 10 to inform the User that Revival cannot be applied to the Notice(s). If all Suspensions are eligible for Revival, PLUS proceeds to Step 6. |
| 6 | Redirect to Revival Detail Page | The Staff Portal redirects the user to the Revival Detail Page so that the User can input the Revival details, such as: Select Revival Reason Input Revival Remarks (if any) |
| 7 | Input Revival Details &amp; submit | The user enters required suspension revival information and submits the form. *Note: For bulk Revivals, the same Revival Reason and Revival Remark will be used for all Suspensions and Notices. |
| 8 | Send Revival request to backend | The Staff Portal sends the revival request to the OCMS backend system for processing. |
| 9 | Backend checks and processes Revival request | The OCMS backend validates and processes the revival request based on the pre-defined logic. If one or more Suspensions cannot be revived, the OCMS Staff Portal backend responds to the Staff Portal with an error message. If the Suspension is eligible for Revival, the OCMS will revive the Suspension and perform the corresponding follow-up action. After the process is completed, OCMS backend responds to the Staff Portal with a success message. |
| 10 | Staff Portal displays PS Success or Fail Message | The Staff Portal displays a message showing whether the Revival was successfully applied or failed. |
| 11 | End | The process concludes. |
